Nexus is a slightly unusual Wolfenstein scenario. Unlike a more standard scenario, your goal isn't just to find a lift that will take you to the next level. Indeed, Nexus has several exits, most of which are easy to find, and all of which are fully functional. But all but one of these lifts loop you back to the beginning of the level!\
\
Your goal is to find the real lift. Only one lift panel will break you out of the loop, and send you to the Victory screen. But that lift is carefully hidden.\
\
Nexus is divided into four quadrants. Each quadrant is designed to be a pastiche of a different scenario by the designer Laz Rojas. The aim is not just to make the quadrants look like these scenarios but, through careful attention to design and layout, to really make them feel like the scenarios they're based on. The aim is to make each quadrant feel like you're stepping into one of those scenarios briefly, playing through material that could have been designed by Laz himself! I'd like to think I've gone a little way towards that goal.\
\
