\cf0 \ulnone If you're not sure how to move at the start of the level, here's a hint from Clubey:\
\
"Sometimes a single mouse can be more of an ally than whole prides of lions!"\
\
In other words, don't use your keyboard. Give a quick nudge of the mouse instead! The player moves slightly faster when moved by the mouse, and this gives the player enough momentum to escape the starting position. Which direction you move chooses which path you'll play, though. So choose wisely! Or just give the mouse a spin and see what you end up with!\
\
You can win regardless of which direction you start out on, although some routes are easier than others. It's even possible to win without fighting a single boss, but it's difficult!\
\
You can use the looping nature of Nexus to your advantage. Don't be afraid to use the looping lifts to reset the level. While this will reset the enemies, this will also reset the ammo and health caches. You can use this to build up your supplies if you need to tackle nastier enemies!\
\
Nexus uses up a lot of the map, and not much space is wasted. If you see a spot on the map that looks like it is unused, do a scout around for secrets! You might just find a way in!\
\
All rooms hidden behind impassable objects can be explored. Use this to guide your explorations!\
\
In order to fully explore the level, you'll need to find a number of secrets. Don't be concerned, though! All of these are marked. Secrets required to finish the level are indicated by special wall or object markings. But some special secrets leading to bonus caches are instead indicated by the map geography. Keep your eyes open!\
